1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:04,120
Her torch has never gone out. Since nineteen ninety...

2
00:00:04,170 --> 00:00:07,490
at every American World Cup match... she has been standing there. Watching.

3
00:00:07,540 --> 00:00:10,860
Waiting for this exact night.

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:14,620
Tonight, Liberty comes home.

5
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:20,485
In episode three, we PREDICTED respect in Toronto — no goals, one swap of shirts.

6
00:00:20,535 --> 00:00:24,520
Tonight... it is America's turn.

7
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:30,050
Welcome back to WorldCup twenty-six Legends, episode four.

8
00:00:30,100 --> 00:00:34,150
The United States versus Paraguay. Group D. AT&T Stadium, Texas.

9
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,920
Eighty thousand voices under one colossal roof. And hiding inside this fixture...

10
00:00:39,970 --> 00:00:43,890
is the oldest secret in World Cup history.

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:50,540
Listen carefully. The year is nineteen thirty. The very FIRST World Cup.

12
00:00:50,590 --> 00:00:54,630
And in Montevideo... the United States face Paraguay.

13
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:58,907
America wins three nil.

14
00:00:58,957 --> 00:01:01,363
And a twenty-year-old named Bert Patenaude scores all three...

15
00:01:01,413 --> 00:01:03,820
the first hat-trick in World Cup history.

16
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:12,800
But here is the twist: for seventy-six years, the record books gave that honor to an Argentine.

17
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:19,485
Only in two thousand six did FIFA finally correct it. The first hat-trick ever...

18
00:01:19,535 --> 00:01:23,520
belongs to an American. Against Paraguay.

19
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,780
Ninety-six years later... the rematch. Same two nations. Biggest stage on Earth.

20
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:39,900
Meet the hosts. The golden generation that promised America a football future...

21
00:01:39,950 --> 00:01:43,050
and now has to deliver it.

22
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:48,645
Christian Pulisic. The captain.

23
00:01:48,695 --> 00:01:52,840
He carried American soccer from its darkest hours to this very night — and Milan made him sharper than ever.

24
00:01:54,500 --> 00:01:58,435
Folarin Balogun, the cold-blooded number nine.

25
00:01:58,485 --> 00:02:02,420
Weston McKennie, the engine that never stops. Tyler Adams, the heartbeat.

26
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:08,615
A home World Cup. Eighty thousand believers.

27
00:02:08,665 --> 00:02:11,280
No more promises — tonight they deliver.

28
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,895
But Paraguay is the quietest team in Group D. No hype. No headlines.

29
00:02:17,945 --> 00:02:21,840
Just cold-eyed steel from South American qualifying.

30
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:27,625
Miguel Almiron — six years in the Premier League.

31
00:02:27,675 --> 00:02:30,800
He knows these American stadiums... intimately.

32
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:36,395
Julio Enciso, the young wizard from Brighton, dances with the recklessness of youth.

33
00:02:36,445 --> 00:02:40,340
And Gustavo Gomez... is simply a wall.

34
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,970
They know Pulisic. They know the machine. And they are not afraid.

35
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:54,255
So here is the duel: the Captain against the Wonderkid. Pulisic's burden...

36
00:02:54,305 --> 00:02:59,060
against Enciso's freedom. The weight of hosting against nothing to lose.

37
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:03,910
And our prediction — built on that history, on home pressure, and on Paraguay's iron defense.

38
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:07,370
Watch.

39
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:12,995
Thirty-fourth minute. Pulisic feints, explodes, and slides it across — BALOGUN!

40
00:03:13,045 --> 00:03:17,540
One nil! AT&T Stadium detonates!

41
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:21,453
But remember the steel.

42
00:03:21,503 --> 00:03:24,457
Sixty-first minute — Almiron, the man who knows America best, silences eighty thousand.

43
00:03:24,507 --> 00:03:27,460
One — one.

44
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,590
And then... the seventy-eighth minute arrives.

45
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:35,230
The Texas heat presses down like a hand.

46
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:42,730
Pulisic surges — Gomez blocks — and the ball falls... to Enciso. Forty yards out.

47
00:03:42,780 --> 00:03:47,510
He looks up. The American defense is scrambling.

48
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:54,600
And right here... the story stops. Because what happens next decides everything.

49
00:03:56,500 --> 00:04:00,135
So tell us YOUR ending. Comment ONE if it stays one-one.

50
00:04:00,185 --> 00:04:03,820
Comment TWO if the kid from Brighton breaks eighty thousand hearts.

51
00:04:05,500 --> 00:04:09,185
Our call: the hosts survive. One-one. Walls like Gomez bend...

52
00:04:09,235 --> 00:04:12,920
but Texas nights do not break.

53
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:20,065
And now — remember her? Legend number four: The Liberty Fan.

54
00:04:20,115 --> 00:04:25,680
Every American World Cup match since nineteen ninety. The flame never went out.

55
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:30,290
Tonight, it burned brighter than ever. Collect her inside the game.

56
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,247
Which brings us to YOU.

57
00:04:35,297 --> 00:04:38,043
At WorldCup twenty-six dot world, pick three of the forty-eight nations — and every goal they score...

58
00:04:38,093 --> 00:04:40,840
scores for you.

59
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:49,600
Free to play. Live leaderboard. Underdogs pay triple. Your picks change everything.

60
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:54,395
Hit like — send this to the friend who doubts American soccer.

61
00:04:54,445 --> 00:04:58,640
And subscribe: next... BRAZIL. And we saw magic.

